    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Rear Cover - Removal</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Removal</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Ring Gear Runout Check</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, check flywheel surface runout. These checks are performed to ensure
                        proper engine to transmission alignment. Failure to ensure proper bore concentricity and face
                        runout may result in reduced clutch and/or transmission life.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check for ring gear damage associated with the starter pinion. If damage is found, skip
                    ring gear surface run out check. Flywheel should be replaced.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj07/J07002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Checking ring gear for a run out condition (typical)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure flywheel ring gear for surface run out.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Keep the crankshaft end play at zero in the same direction for all measurements.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <seqlist>
                <item>
                    <para>Attach a Dial Indicator with Magnetic Base onto engine. Place dial indicator tip against
                        surface of ring gear. See
                        <hotlnk document="eges3001_293.xml" xrefid="E30014C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Zero the dial indicator.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Rotate crankshaft slowly (clockwise) and record total indicator runout. See
                        <hotlnk document="eges3001_291.xml" xrefid="E30014A">Specifications</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace ring gear if total indicator runout has been determined to be out of
                    specifications.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
